stormpot

Class AllocThread_NullPollFromLiveWhileShrinking_TestTemplate<SLOT,ALLOC_THREAD extends Runnable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stormpot.AllocThread_NullPollFromLiveWhileShrinking_TestTemplate<SLOT,ALLOC_THREAD>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BAllocThread_NullPollFromLiveWhileShrinking_Test, QAllocThread_NullPollFromLiveWhileShrinking_Test

    public abstract class AllocThread_NullPollFromLiveWhileShrinking_TestTemplate<SLOT,ALLOC_THREAD extends Runnable>
extends Object

    This is a rather esoteric case. It turned out that when a queue-based Pool was resized to become smaller, and the pool was already depleted, then it was possible for the *AllocThread to pull a null from the live queue, and try to deallocate it. This is obviously not good, because it would kill the allocation thread, halting all meaningful function of the pool.

    Writing a test for this, as you can probably guess, was not easy.

    Author:
    Chris Vest <mr.chrisvest@gmail.com>
